definition.value: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having N(2),N(2)-dimethylguanosine as the nucleobase.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic monophosphate analogue having imidazo[2,1-b]purin-4-one as the modified nucleobase.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cGMP in which the nitrogen atom at position 7 on the purine fragment is replaced by a methine (C-H) group
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic GMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 4-chlorophenylthio group.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic GMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylthio group.

A diphenyldiazene compound having two amino substituents at the 2- and 4-positions and an aminosulphonyl substituent at the 4'-position. It was the first antibacterial drug, (introduced 1935) and the first of the sulfonamide antibiotics.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having guanine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromoguanine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having guanine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as icosanoyl.
An O-tetradecenoyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as myristoleoyl.
An O-tetradecenoyl-L-carnitine  in which the acyl group is specified as (5Z)-tetradecenoyl.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (5Z)-tetradecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl.

An organyl group consisting of a hexasaccharide chain of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked (1->2) or (1->3), linked glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.

A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of the hexasaccharide beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/16:0).
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as 4,8-dimethylnonanoyl.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as 3-oxopalmitoyl.

A alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosylceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl).
A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to the Cer(d18:1/20:0).
A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/22:0).
A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 54 carbons and 3 double bonds.

A hydrochloride that is the monohydrochloride salt of propafenone. It is a class 1C antiarrhythmic drug with local anesthetic effects, and is used in the management of supraventricular and ventricular arrhythmias.
A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 52 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 52 carbons and 3 double bonds.
A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 50 carbons and 2 double bonds.

An organyl group consisting of a disaccharide of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked (1->3), linked glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.
A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 50 carbons and 1 double bond.
A cholestenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (25S)-3-oxocholest-4-en-26-oic acid.
A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/24:0).
A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/24:1(15Z)).
A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.
A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any phosphatidylethanol; major species at pH 7.3.
A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.
A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of  beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/16:0).
A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/18:0).
A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/20:0).
A mixture composed from 2' and 3'-O-(N-methylanthraniloyl) derivatives of GDP in unspecified amounts.

An organyl group consisting of a trisaccharide of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2) and (1->3), and linked at the reducing end glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.
A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/22:0).

An organyl group consisting of a trisaccharide of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->2), and linked at the reducing end glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.
A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/24:0).

A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to the Cer(d18:1/18:0).

A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to the Cer(d18:1/22:0).
Any homopolysaccharide composed of rhamnose residues.

A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of the hexasaccharide beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/18:0).
